@startuml Sequence_Order_Placement

actor Customer
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB
participant "Payment Gateway" as Payment

== Customer Places Order ==

Customer -> Frontend: Login
Frontend -> API: POST /api/auth/login
API -> DB: Verify credentials
DB --> API: User data
API --> Frontend: Auth token
Frontend --> Customer: Dashboard

Customer -> Frontend: Browse Fabrics
Frontend -> API: GET /api/fabrics
API -> DB: Fetch fabrics
DB --> API: Fabric list
API --> Frontend: Fabric data
Frontend --> Customer: Display fabrics

Customer -> Frontend: Select Fabric & Enter Details
Frontend -> Frontend: Validate form

Customer -> Frontend: Place Order
Frontend -> API: POST /api/orders\n(customerId, items, fabric, measurements)
API -> DB: Check fabric stock
DB --> API: Stock available

API -> DB: Create Order
DB --> API: Order created

API -> DB: Update fabric stock
DB --> API: Stock updated

API -> DB: Save measurement snapshot
DB --> API: Measurements saved

API -> Payment: Create payment session
Payment --> API: Payment link

API --> Frontend: Order created + Payment link
Frontend --> Customer: Order confirmation\n+ Payment page

== Payment Processing ==

Customer -> Payment: Make Payment
Payment -> Payment: Process payment
Payment --> API: Payment webhook
API -> DB: Update order status
API -> DB: Create/Update Bill
DB --> API: Bill updated

API -> DB: Create notification
DB --> API: Notification created

API --> Frontend: Payment success
Frontend --> Customer: Payment confirmation

note right of DB
  Order Status: "Order Placed"
  Bill Status: "Paid"
end note

@enduml


